The paper deals with bidimensionality theory, which is a tool used to obtain subexponential time parameterized algorithms on graphs. This suggests that the paper may belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category. The paper also discusses the existence of linear kernels for parameterized problems, which falls under the scope of cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry). The use of Countable Monadic Second Order Logic (CMSO) in the paper suggests a connection to cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics).
